The Spring 2021 White House Internship Program application is now open. The application portal will be open until August 28, 2020, and applications received after the deadline will not be considered. The internship term will run from January 27 to April 16, 2021, and application decisions will be announced during the week of November 9. Applicants must be at least 18 years old, United States citizens, and able to commit to the full internship term. The selection process is highly competitive and based on demonstrated commitment to public service, leadership, and the mission of the Trump Administration. For more information and frequently asked questions, visit the White House website.